You are implementing RECO-753: April Promo Drinkware & Bags endpoint in a NestJS project.

**Working directory:** /Users/4thwithme/Documents/repo/recommendations-service-RECO-753

## What to build

Add a `GET /april-promo` endpoint to the existing promos module. Follow the EXACT pattern of the March Promo endpoint.

## Files to create/modify

### 1. CREATE: `src/modules/rest/promos/dto/april-promo-query.dto.ts`

Follow the March Promo DTO pattern exactly. Here's the March version for reference:

```typescript
import { ApiPropertyOptional } from '@nestjs/swagger';
import { Type } from 'class-transformer';
import { IsIn, IsInt, IsOptional, Max, Min } from 'class-validator';

const ALLOWED_MARCH_PROMO_CATEGORY_IDS = [218, 8, 188, 521, 920, 405];

export class MarchPromoQueryDto {
	@ApiPropertyOptional({
		description: 'Number of products to return',
		example: 20,
		default: 20,
	})
	@IsOptional()
	@Type(() => Number)
	@IsInt({ message: 'Limit must be an integer' })
	@Min(1, { message: 'Limit must be greater than 0' })
	@Max(100, { message: 'Limit must be less than or equal to 100' })
	limit?: number;

	@ApiPropertyOptional({
		description:
			'Category ID to filter products. Allowed: 218 (Promotional Products), 8 (Pens & Office Supplies), 188 (Technology), 521 (Pens & Writing), 920 (Stationery), 405 (Stickers & Magnets)',
		example: 8,
		default: 8,
	})
	@IsOptional()
	@Type(() => Number)
	@IsInt({ message: 'categoryId must be an integer' })
	@IsIn(ALLOWED_MARCH_PROMO_CATEGORY_IDS, {
		message: `categoryId must be one of: ${ALLOWED_MARCH_PROMO_CATEGORY_IDS.join(', ')}`,
	})
	categoryId?: number;
}
```

For April Promo, use these categories:
- Drinkware: 477 (All Drinkware), 6 (Mugs), 43 (Water Bottles), 407 (Tumblers), 42 (Can Coolers), 58 (Glassware), 7 (Plastic Cups), 722 (KOOZIE)
- Bags: 482 (All Bags), 37 (Tote Bags), 203 (Backpacks), 73 (Drawstring Bags), 41 (Duffels & Gym Bags), 77 (Lunch Bags & Coolers), 238 (Fanny Packs), 450 (Pouches)

Default category: 477 (All Drinkware)

The description should list: "Category ID to filter products. Allowed: 477 (All Drinkware), 6 (Mugs), 43 (Water Bottles), 407 (Tumblers), 42 (Can Coolers), 58 (Glassware), 7 (Plastic Cups), 722 (KOOZIE), 482 (All Bags), 37 (Tote Bags), 203 (Backpacks), 73 (Drawstring Bags), 41 (Duffels & Gym Bags), 77 (Lunch Bags & Coolers), 238 (Fanny Packs), 450 (Pouches)"

### 2. MODIFY: `src/modules/rest/promos/promos.controller.ts`

Add a new endpoint method `getAprilPromoProducts` following the March promo pattern:

```typescript
@Get('april-promo')
@HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)
@ApiOperation({
    summary: 'Get april promo products',
    description:
        'Returns trending products filtered by category for the April Drinkware & Bags promotion. Allowed categories: 477 (All Drinkware), 6 (Mugs), 43 (Water Bottles), 407 (Tumblers), 42 (Can Coolers), 58 (Glassware), 7 (Plastic Cups), 722 (KOOZIE), 482 (All Bags), 37 (Tote Bags), 203 (Backpacks), 73 (Drawstring Bags), 41 (Duffels & Gym Bags), 77 (Lunch Bags & Coolers), 238 (Fanny Packs), 450 (Pouches).',
})
@ApiOkResponse({
    description: 'Successfully retrieved april promo products',
    type: PromoResponseDto,
})
async getAprilPromoProducts(
    @Query() query: AprilPromoQueryDto,
): Promise<PromoResponseDto> {
    return await this.promosService.getAprilPromoProducts({
        limit: query.limit,
        categoryId: query.categoryId,
    });
}
```

Add the import for `AprilPromoQueryDto` at the top.

### 3. MODIFY: `src/modules/rest/promos/promos.service.ts`

Add a new method `getAprilPromoProducts` following the March promo pattern. Use `getTrendingProductsByCategory` (NOT `getTrendingProductsByCategoryAndStyleIds` since we don't have a curated product list).

Add constant: `private readonly APRIL_PROMO_DEFAULT_CATEGORY_ID = 477;`

The method should:
1. Call `this.forecastedTrendingProductsService.getTrendingProductsByCategory({ categoryId, limit: 100 })`
2. Hydrate products with colors
3. Assign random colors
4. Slice to limit
5. Return PromoResponseDto

Follow the March promo pattern for hydration/color logic. The key difference: use `getTrendingProductsByCategory` instead of `getTrendingProductsByCategoryAndStyleIds`.

Add `@LogExecution` decorator matching the March promo pattern.

## CRITICAL RULES
- NO comments in code (except ESLint disable)
- Named parameters (object destructured) for ALL functions
- Import aliases only (@modules/, @utils/, etc.)
- @LogExecution on service methods
- Explicit return types on all functions
- Logger from @nestjs/common, never console.log
- Swagger decorators on endpoints
- Match the EXACT code style of the existing March promo code
- Use tabs for indentation (match existing files)

## After implementation, commit with message:
`RECO-753: Add April Promo endpoint for Drinkware & Bags`

Do NOT run tests. Just implement and commit.

